  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. The term <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>4</sup> can be factored as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x squared, times, x squared\"></span>. Factoring &ndash;6 as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"2 times negative 3\"></span> yields values that add to &ndash;1, the coefficient of <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> in the expression.<p>Choices A, C, and D are incorrect and may result from finding factors of &ndash;6 that don&rsquo;t add to the coefficient of <span class=\"italic\">x</span><sup>2</sup> in the original expression.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
